criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. diagnosis of mild to moderate Alzheimer dementia;

          2. aged over 65 years old in both gender;

          3. MMSE score between 14 and 26;

          4. adequate vision and hearing ability to complete all study tests;

          5. with a stable caregiver.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. a medical history of other dementia types, like Frontotemporal dementia, Dementia with
             Lewy Bodies, Vascular Dementia, and mixed type, et al;

          2. known of other neurological diseases, cranial nervous system cancer

          3. severe liver or kidney dysfunction (alanine aminotransferase＞200 IU/L, aspartate
             transaminase＞200 IU/L or serum creatinine ＞2.5 mg/dl);

          4. severe cardiovascular disease (heart failure, coronary heart disease)
